52 /* the default value of endianess to be used, if none's specified */
53 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_DEFAULT DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_BIG

55 /* the base to be used if string mode is specified. These options would be
56  * specified in DetectByteParseData->base */
57 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_NONE 0
58 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_HEX 16
59 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_DEC 10
60 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_OCT 8

62 /* the default value for multiplier. Either ways we always store a
63  * multiplier, 1 or otherwise, so that we can always multiply the extracted
64  * value and store it, instead of checking if a multiplier is set or not */
65 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_DEFAULT 1
66 /* the min/max limit for multiplier */
67 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_MIN_LIMIT 1
68 #define DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_MAX_LIMIT 65535

70 /* the max no of bytes that can be extracted in string mode - (string, hex)
71  * (string, oct) or (string, dec) */
72 #define STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_OCT 23
73 #define STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_DEC 20
74 #define STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_HEX 14
75 /* the max no of bytes that can be extraced in non-string mode */
76 #define NO_STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT 8

78 #define PARSE_REGEX "^" \
79  "\\s*([0-9]+)\\s*" \
80  ",\\s*(-?[0-9]+)\\s*" \
81  ",\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s*" \
82  "(?:(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s*)|(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s+([^\\s,]+)\\s*))?" \
83  "(?:(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s*)|(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s+([^\\s,]+)\\s*))?" \
84  "(?:(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s*)|(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s+([^\\s,]+)\\s*))?" \
85  "(?:(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s*)|(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s+([^\\s,]+)\\s*))?" \
86  "(?:(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s*)|(?:,\\s*([^\\s,]+)\\s+([^\\s,]+)\\s*))?" \
87  "$"

98 /**
99  * \brief Registers the keyword handlers for the "byte_extract" keyword.
100  */
101 void DetectByteExtractRegister(void)
102 {
103  const char *eb;
104  int eo;
105  int opts = 0;
106 
107  sigmatch_table[DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT].name = "byte_extract";
108  sigmatch_table[DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT].Match = NULL;
109  sigmatch_table[DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT].AppLayerMatch = NULL;
110  sigmatch_table[DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT].Setup = DetectByteExtractSetup;
111  sigmatch_table[DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT].Free = DetectByteExtractFree;
112  sigmatch_table[DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT].RegisterTests = DetectByteExtractRegisterTests;
113 
114  sigmatch_table[DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT].flags |= SIGMATCH_PAYLOAD;
115 
116  parse_regex = pcre_compile(PARSE_REGEX, opts, &eb, &eo, NULL);
117  if (parse_regex == NULL) {
118  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_COMPILE, "pcre compile of \"%s\" failed "
119  "at offset %" PRId32 ": %s", PARSE_REGEX, eo, eb);
120  goto error;
121  }
122 
123  parse_regex_study = pcre_study(parse_regex, 0, &eb);
124  if (eb != NULL) {
125  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_STUDY, "pcre study failed: %s", eb);
126  goto error;
127  }
128 
129  return;
130  error:
131  return;
132 }

134 int DetectByteExtractDoMatch(DetectEngineThreadCtx *det_ctx, SigMatch *sm,
135  Signature *s, uint8_t *payload,
136  uint16_t payload_len, uint64_t *value,
137  uint8_t endian)
138 {
139  DetectByteExtractData *data = (DetectByteExtractData *)sm->ctx;
140  uint8_t *ptr = NULL;
141  int32_t len = 0;
142  uint64_t val = 0;
143  int extbytes;
144 
145  if (payload_len == 0) {
146  return 0;
147  }
148 
149  /* Calculate the ptr value for the bytetest and length remaining in
150  * the packet from that point.
151  */
152  if (data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_RELATIVE) {
153  SCLogDebug("relative, working with det_ctx->buffer_offset %"PRIu32", "
154  "data->offset %"PRIu32"", det_ctx->buffer_offset, data->offset);
155 
156  ptr = payload + det_ctx->buffer_offset;
157  len = payload_len - det_ctx->buffer_offset;
158 
159  ptr += data->offset;
160  len -= data->offset;
161 
162  /* No match if there is no relative base */
163  if (len <= 0) {
164  return 0;
165  }
166  //PrintRawDataFp(stdout,ptr,len);
167  } else {
168  SCLogDebug("absolute, data->offset %"PRIu32"", data->offset);
169 
170  ptr = payload + data->offset;
171  len = payload_len - data->offset;
172  }
173 
174  /* Validate that the to-be-extracted is within the packet */
175  if (ptr < payload || data->nbytes > len) {
176  SCLogDebug("Data not within payload pkt=%p, ptr=%p, len=%"PRIu32", nbytes=%d",
177  payload, ptr, len, data->nbytes);
178  return 0;
179  }
180 
181  /* Extract the byte data */
182  if (data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING) {
183  extbytes = ByteExtractStringUint64(&val, data->base,
184  data->nbytes, (const char *)ptr);
185  if (extbytes <= 0) {
186  /* strtoull() return 0 if there is no numeric value in data string */
187  if (val == 0) {
188  SCLogDebug("No Numeric value");
189  return 0;
190  } else {
191  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_NUM_BYTES, "Error extracting %d "
192  "bytes of string data: %d", data->nbytes, extbytes);
193  return -1;
194  }
195  }
196  } else {
197  int endianness = (endian == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_BIG) ?
198  BYTE_BIG_ENDIAN : BYTE_LITTLE_ENDIAN;
199  extbytes = ByteExtractUint64(&val, endianness, data->nbytes, ptr);
200  if (extbytes != data->nbytes) {
201  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_NUM_BYTES, "Error extracting %d bytes "
202  "of numeric data: %d\n", data->nbytes, extbytes);
203  return 0;
204  }
205  }
206 
207  /* Adjust the jump value based on flags */
208  val *= data->multiplier_value;
209  if (data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ALIGN) {
210  if ((val % data->align_value) != 0) {
211  val += data->align_value - (val % data->align_value);
212  }
213  }
214 
215  ptr += extbytes;
216 
217  det_ctx->buffer_offset = ptr - payload;
218 
219  *value = val;
220 
221  return 1;
222 }

228  goto end;

230  return 1;

233 /**
234  * \internal
235  * \brief Used to parse byte_extract arg.
236  *
237  * \arg The argument to parse.
238  *
239  * \param bed On success an instance containing the parsed data.
240  * On failure, NULL.
241  */
242 static inline DetectByteExtractData *DetectByteExtractParse(char *arg)
243 {
244  DetectByteExtractData *bed = NULL;
245 #define MAX_SUBSTRINGS 100
246  int ret = 0, res = 0;
247  int ov[MAX_SUBSTRINGS];
248  int i = 0;
249 
250  ret = pcre_exec(parse_regex, parse_regex_study, arg,
251  strlen(arg), 0, 0, ov, MAX_SUBSTRINGS);
252  if (ret < 3 || ret > 19) {
253  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_PARSE, "parse error, ret %" PRId32
254  ", string \"%s\"", ret, arg);
255  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Invalid arg to byte_extract : %s "
256  "for byte_extract", arg);
257  goto error;
258  }
259 
260  bed = SCMalloc(sizeof(DetectByteExtractData));
261  if (unlikely(bed == NULL))
262  goto error;
263  memset(bed, 0, sizeof(DetectByteExtractData));
264 
265  /* no of bytes to extract */
266  char nbytes_str[64] = "";
267  res = pcre_copy_substring((char *)arg, ov,
268  MAX_SUBSTRINGS, 1, nbytes_str, sizeof(nbytes_str));
269  if (res < 0) {
270  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_GET_SUBSTRING, "pcre_copy_substring failed "
271  "for arg 1 for byte_extract");
272  goto error;
273  }
274  bed->nbytes = atoi(nbytes_str);
275 
276  /* offset */
277  char offset_str[64] = "";
278  res = pcre_copy_substring((char *)arg, ov,
279  MAX_SUBSTRINGS, 2, offset_str, sizeof(offset_str));
280  if (res < 0) {
281  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_GET_SUBSTRING, "pcre_copy_substring failed "
282  "for arg 2 for byte_extract");
283  goto error;
284  }
285  int offset = atoi(offset_str);
286  if (offset < -65535 || offset > 65535) {
287  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "byte_extract offset invalid - %d. "
288  "The right offset range is -65535 to 65535", offset);
289  goto error;
290  }
291  bed->offset = offset;
292 
293  /* var name */
294  char varname_str[256] = "";
295  res = pcre_copy_substring((char *)arg, ov,
296  MAX_SUBSTRINGS, 3, varname_str, sizeof(varname_str));
297  if (res < 0) {
298  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_GET_SUBSTRING, "pcre_copy_substring failed "
299  "for arg 3 for byte_extract");
300  goto error;
301  }
302  bed->name = SCStrdup(varname_str);
303  if (bed->name == NULL)
304  goto error;
305 
306  /* check out other optional args */
307  for (i = 4; i < ret; i++) {
308  char opt_str[64] = "";
309  res = pcre_copy_substring((char *)arg, ov,
310  MAX_SUBSTRINGS, i, opt_str, sizeof(opt_str));
311  if (res < 0) {
312  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_GET_SUBSTRING, "pcre_copy_substring failed "
313  "for arg %d for byte_extract", i);
314  goto error;
315  }
316 
317  if (strcmp("relative", opt_str) == 0) {
318  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_RELATIVE) {
319  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "relative specified more "
320  "than once for byte_extract");
321  goto error;
322  }
323  bed->flags |= DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_RELATIVE;
324  } else if (strcmp("multiplier", opt_str) == 0) {
325  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_MULTIPLIER) {
326  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "multiplier specified more "
327  "than once for byte_extract");
328  goto error;
329  }
330  bed->flags |= DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_MULTIPLIER;
331  i++;
332 
333  char multiplier_str[16] = "";
334  res = pcre_copy_substring((char *)arg, ov,
335  MAX_SUBSTRINGS, i, multiplier_str, sizeof(multiplier_str));
336  if (res < 0) {
337  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_GET_SUBSTRING, "pcre_copy_substring failed "
338  "for arg %d for byte_extract", i);
339  goto error;
340  }
341  int multiplier = atoi(multiplier_str);
342  if (multiplier < DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_MIN_LIMIT ||
343  multiplier > DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_MAX_LIMIT) {
344  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "multipiler_value invalid "
345  "- %d. The range is %d-%d",
346  multiplier,
347  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_MIN_LIMIT,
348  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_MAX_LIMIT);
349  goto error;
350  }
351  bed->multiplier_value = multiplier;
352  } else if (strcmp("big", opt_str) == 0) {
353  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ENDIAN) {
354  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "endian option specified "
355  "more than once for byte_extract");
356  goto error;
357  }
358  bed->flags |= DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ENDIAN;
359  bed->endian = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_BIG;
360  } else if (strcmp("little", opt_str) == 0) {
361  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ENDIAN) {
362  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "endian option specified "
363  "more than once for byte_extract");
364  goto error;
365  }
366  bed->flags |= DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ENDIAN;
367  bed->endian = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_LITTLE;
368  } else if (strcmp("dce", opt_str) == 0) {
369  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ENDIAN) {
370  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "endian option specified "
371  "more than once for byte_extract");
372  goto error;
373  }
374  bed->flags |= DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ENDIAN;
375  bed->endian = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_DCE;
376  } else if (strcmp("string", opt_str) == 0) {
377  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING) {
378  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "string specified more "
379  "than once for byte_extract");
380  goto error;
381  }
382  if (bed->base != DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_NONE) {
383  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "The right way to specify "
384  "base is (string, base) and not (base, string) "
385  "for byte_extract");
386  goto error;
387  }
388  bed->flags |= DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING;
389  } else if (strcmp("hex", opt_str) == 0) {
390  if (!(bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING)) {
391  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Base(hex) specified "
392  "without specifying string. The right way is "
393  "(string, base) and not (base, string)");
394  goto error;
395  }
396  if (bed->base != DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_NONE) {
397  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "More than one base "
398  "specified for byte_extract");
399  goto error;
400  }
401  bed->base = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_HEX;
402  } else if (strcmp("oct", opt_str) == 0) {
403  if (!(bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING)) {
404  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Base(oct) specified "
405  "without specifying string. The right way is "
406  "(string, base) and not (base, string)");
407  goto error;
408  }
409  if (bed->base != DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_NONE) {
410  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "More than one base "
411  "specified for byte_extract");
412  goto error;
413  }
414  bed->base = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_OCT;
415  } else if (strcmp("dec", opt_str) == 0) {
416  if (!(bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING)) {
417  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Base(dec) specified "
418  "without specifying string. The right way is "
419  "(string, base) and not (base, string)");
420  goto error;
421  }
422  if (bed->base != DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_NONE) {
423  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "More than one base "
424  "specified for byte_extract");
425  goto error;
426  }
427  bed->base = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_DEC;
428  } else if (strcmp("align", opt_str) == 0) {
429  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ALIGN) {
430  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Align specified more "
431  "than once for byte_extract");
432  goto error;
433  }
434  bed->flags |= DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ALIGN;
435  i++;
436 
437  char align_str[16] = "";
438  res = pcre_copy_substring((char *)arg, ov,
439  MAX_SUBSTRINGS, i, align_str, sizeof(align_str));
440  if (res < 0) {
441  SCLogError(SC_ERR_PCRE_GET_SUBSTRING, "pcre_copy_substring failed "
442  "for arg %d in byte_extract", i);
443  goto error;
444  }
445  bed->align_value = atoi(align_str);
446  if (!(bed->align_value == 2 || bed->align_value == 4)) {
447  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Invalid align_value for "
448  "byte_extract - \"%d\"", bed->align_value);
449  goto error;
450  }
451  } else if (strcmp("", opt_str) == 0) {
452  ;
453  } else {
454  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Invalid option - \"%s\" "
455  "specified in byte_extract", opt_str);
456  goto error;
457  }
458  } /* for (i = 4; i < ret; i++) */
459 
460  /* validation */
461  if (!(bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_MULTIPLIER)) {
462  /* default value */
463  bed->multiplier_value = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_MULTIPLIER_DEFAULT;
464  }
465 
466  if (bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING) {
467  if (bed->base == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_NONE) {
468  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Base not specified for "
469  "byte_extract, though string was specified. "
470  "The right options are (string, hex), (string, oct) "
471  "or (string, dec)");
472  goto error;
473  }
474  if (bed->endian != DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_NONE) {
475  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "byte_extract can't have "
476  "endian \"big\" or \"little\" specified along with "
477  "\"string\"");
478  goto error;
479  }
480  if (bed->base == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_OCT) {
481  /* if are dealing with octal nos, the max no that can fit in a 8
482  * byte value is 01777777777777777777777 */
483  if (bed->nbytes > STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_OCT) {
484  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "byte_extract can't process "
485  "more than %d bytes in \"string\" extraction",
486  STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_OCT);
487  goto error;
488  }
489  } else if (bed->base == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_DEC) {
490  /* if are dealing with decimal nos, the max no that can fit in a 8
491  * byte value is 18446744073709551615 */
492  if (bed->nbytes > STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_DEC) {
493  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "byte_extract can't process "
494  "more than %d bytes in \"string\" extraction",
495  STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_DEC);
496  goto error;
497  }
498  } else if (bed->base == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_HEX) {
499  /* if are dealing with hex nos, the max no that can fit in a 8
500  * byte value is 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF */
501  if (bed->nbytes > STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_HEX) {
502  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "byte_extract can't process "
503  "more than %d bytes in \"string\" extraction",
504  STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT_FOR_HEX);
505  goto error;
506  }
507  } else {
508  ; // just a placeholder. we won't reach here.
509  }
510  } else {
511  if (bed->nbytes > NO_STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT) {
512  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "byte_extract can't process "
513  "more than %d bytes in \"non-string\" extraction",
514  NO_STRING_MAX_BYTES_TO_EXTRACT);
515  goto error;
516  }
517  /* if string has not been specified and no endian option has been
518  * specified, then set the default endian level of BIG */
519  if (!(bed->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_ENDIAN))
520  bed->endian = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_DEFAULT;
521  }
522 
523  return bed;
524  error:
525  if (bed != NULL)
526  DetectByteExtractFree(bed);
527  return NULL;
528 }

530 /**
531  * \brief The setup function for the byte_extract keyword for a signature.
532  *
533  * \param de_ctx Pointer to the detection engine context.
534  * \param s Pointer to signature for the current Signature being parsed
535  * from the rules.
536  * \param m Pointer to the head of the SigMatch for the current rule
537  * being parsed.
538  * \param arg Pointer to the string holding the keyword value.
539  *
540  * \retval 0 On success.
541  * \retval -1 On failure.
542  */
543 int DetectByteExtractSetup(DetectEngineCtx *de_ctx, Signature *s, char *arg)
544 {
545  SigMatch *sm = NULL;
546  SigMatch *prev_pm = NULL;
547  DetectByteExtractData *data = NULL;
548  int ret = -1;
549 
550  data = DetectByteExtractParse(arg);
551  if (data == NULL)
552  goto error;
553 
554  int sm_list;
555  if (s->list != DETECT_SM_LIST_NOTSET) {
556  if (s->list == DETECT_SM_LIST_FILEDATA) {
557  if (data->endian == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_DCE) {
558  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "dce byte_extract specified "
559  "with file_data option set.");
560  goto error;
561  }
562  AppLayerHtpEnableResponseBodyCallback();
563  }
564  sm_list = s->list;
565  s->flags |= SIG_FLAG_APPLAYER;
566  if (data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_RELATIVE) {
567  prev_pm = SigMatchGetLastSMFromLists(s, 4,
568  DETECT_CONTENT, s->sm_lists_tail[sm_list],
569  DETECT_PCRE, s->sm_lists_tail[sm_list]);
570  }
571  } else if (data->endian == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_DCE) {
572  if (data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_RELATIVE) {
573  prev_pm = SigMatchGetLastSMFromLists(s, 12,
574  DETECT_CONTENT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH],
575  DETECT_PCRE, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH],
576  DETECT_BYTETEST, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH],
577  DETECT_BYTEJUMP, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH],
578  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH],
579  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH]);
580  if (prev_pm == NULL) {
581  sm_list = DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH;
582  } else {
583  sm_list = SigMatchListSMBelongsTo(s, prev_pm);
584  if (sm_list < 0)
585  goto error;
586  }
587  } else {
588  sm_list = DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH;
589  }
590 
591  s->alproto = ALPROTO_DCERPC;
592  s->flags |= SIG_FLAG_APPLAYER;
593 
594  } else if (data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_RELATIVE) {
595  prev_pm = SigMatchGetLastSMFromLists(s, 168,
596  DETECT_CONTENT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH],
597  DETECT_CONTENT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_UMATCH],

613  DETECT_PCRE, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCBDMATCH],
614  DETECT_PCRE, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_FILEDATA],

666  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSCDMATCH],
667  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HUADMATCH],
668  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHHDMATCH],
669  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHHDMATCH],
670 
671  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH],
672  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_UMATCH],
673  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCBDMATCH],
674  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_FILEDATA],
675  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHDMATCH],
676  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHDMATCH],
677  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HMDMATCH],
678  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HCDMATCH],
679  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRUDMATCH],
680  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSMDMATCH],
681  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HSCDMATCH],
682  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HUADMATCH],
683  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HHHDMATCH],
684  DETECT_ISDATAAT, s->sm_lists_tail[DETECT_SM_LIST_HRHHDMATCH]);
685  if (prev_pm == NULL) {
686  sm_list = DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH;
687  } else {
688  sm_list = SigMatchListSMBelongsTo(s, prev_pm);
689  if (sm_list < 0)
690  goto error;
691  if (sm_list != DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH)
692  s->flags |= SIG_FLAG_APPLAYER;
693  }
694 
695  } else {
696  sm_list = DETECT_SM_LIST_PMATCH;
697  }
698 
699  if (data->endian == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_ENDIAN_DCE) {
700  if (s->alproto != ALPROTO_UNKNOWN && s->alproto != ALPROTO_DCERPC) {
701  SCLogError(SC_ERR_INVALID_SIGNATURE, "Non dce alproto sig has "
702  "byte_extract with dce enabled");
703  goto error;
704  }
705  s->alproto = ALPROTO_DCERPC;
706  if ((data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_STRING) ||
707  (data->base == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_DEC) ||
708  (data->base == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_HEX) ||
709  (data->base == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_BASE_OCT) ) {
710  SCLogError(SC_ERR_CONFLICTING_RULE_KEYWORDS, "Invalid option. "
711  "A byte_jump keyword with dce holds other invalid modifiers.");
712  goto error;
713  }
714  }
715 
716  SigMatch *prev_bed_sm = SigMatchGetLastSMFromLists(s, 2,
717  DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT, s->sm_lists_tail[sm_list]);
718  if (prev_bed_sm == NULL)
719  data->local_id = 0;
720  else
721  data->local_id = ((DetectByteExtractData *)prev_bed_sm->ctx)->local_id + 1;
722  if (data->local_id > de_ctx->byte_extract_max_local_id)
723  de_ctx->byte_extract_max_local_id = data->local_id;
724 
725 
726  sm = SigMatchAlloc();
727  if (sm == NULL)
728  goto error;
729  sm->type = DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT;
730  sm->ctx = (void *)data;
731  SigMatchAppendSMToList(s, sm, sm_list);
732 
733 
734  if (!(data->flags & DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT_FLAG_RELATIVE))
735  goto okay;
736 
737  if (prev_pm == NULL)
738  goto okay;
739 
740  if (prev_pm->type == DETECT_CONTENT) {
741  DetectContentData *cd = (DetectContentData *)prev_pm->ctx;
742  cd->flags |= DETECT_CONTENT_RELATIVE_NEXT;
743  } else if (prev_pm->type == DETECT_PCRE) {
744  DetectPcreData *pd = (DetectPcreData *)prev_pm->ctx;
745  pd->flags |= DETECT_PCRE_RELATIVE_NEXT;
746  }
747 
748  okay:
749  ret = 0;
750  return ret;
751  error:
752  DetectByteExtractFree(data);
753  return ret;
754 }

756 /**
757  * \brief Used to free instances of DetectByteExtractData.
758  *
759  * \param ptr Instance of DetectByteExtractData to be freed.
760  */
761 void DetectByteExtractFree(void *ptr)
762 {
763  if (ptr != NULL) {
764  DetectByteExtractData *bed = ptr;
765  if (bed->name != NULL)
766  SCFree((void *)bed->name);
767  SCFree(bed);
768  }
769 
770  return;
771 }

773 /**
774  * \brief Lookup the SigMatch for a named byte_extract variable.
775  *
776  * \param arg The name of the byte_extract variable to lookup.
777  * \param s Pointer the signature to look in.
778  *
779  * \retval A pointer to the SigMatch if found, otherwise NULL.
780  */
781 SigMatch *DetectByteExtractRetrieveSMVar(const char *arg, Signature *s)
782 {
783  DetectByteExtractData *bed = NULL;
784  int list;
785 
786  for (list = 0; list < DETECT_SM_LIST_MAX; list++) {
787  SigMatch *sm = s->sm_lists[list];
788  while (sm != NULL) {
789  if (sm->type == DETECT_BYTE_EXTRACT) {
790  bed = (DetectByteExtractData *)sm->ctx;
791  if (strcmp(bed->name, arg) == 0) {
792  return sm;
793  }
794  }
795  sm = sm->next;
796  }
797  }
798 
799  return NULL;
800 }
